mtfaWQiOjIwNDYxNzR9/1d120b595949e3a2b44b787a138ce5b338b625317fd435515182dd5=
75a3752ea" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">longtime use<=
/a> of the H-2B visa program at his properties. But the cognitive dissonanc=
e has sent anti-immigration allies scrambling for more sinister explanation=
s. =E2=80=9CEveryone thinks that Steve is right on the substance, but they=
=E2=80=99re too afraid of Elon to push back,=E2=80=9D one source said. =E2=
=80=9CThey need a donor.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">By way of juxtaposition, other=
s have noted the sudden disappearance of <strong>Vivek Ramaswamy</strong>, =
Musk=E2=80=99s DOGE co-chair and co-combatant in the H-1B dustup, who blame=
d America=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cculture of mediocrity=E2=80=9D for a lack of h=
omegrown tech talent. Vivek, who was ubiquitous on social media until that =
episode, hasn=E2=80=99t posted on X since. So far, at least, Ramaswamy is <=
em>not </em>getting a DOGE office next to Musk in the Eisenhower Executive =
Office Building.
In fact, there are reports that he=E2=80=99s being pushed as a candidate fo=
r <strong>J.D. Vance</strong>=E2=80=99s open Senate seat in Ohio=E2=80=94pe=
rhaps a backhanded reward that simultaneously banishes him from the inner c=
ircle. In any case, I=E2=80=99m told, Ramaswamy is being iced out.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-b=
ottom:0px;">The most public outcry over Musk=E2=80=99s betrayal has been li=
mited to the fringe, such as far-right personality <strong>Laura Loomer</st=
rong>, the racist
conspiracy theorist who lost her verified status on X after attacking Musk =
over the H-1B issue. Since then, she told me, she=E2=80=99s seen her profil=
e visits decrease by 83 percent=E2=80=94resulting in a $10,000 per month lo=
ss of revenue on the platform. Now she, too, is crying oligarchy. =E2=80=9C=
The Republican Party has been bought out by tech billionaires, so they=E2=
=80=99re not going to say anything about it,=E2=80=9D Loomer said=E2=80=94n=
oting that some of Trumpworld=E2=80=99s biggest immigration hawks, includin=
g <strong>Stephen
Miller</strong>,<strong> Donald Trump Jr.</strong>, and Vance, stayed consp=
icuously silent during the social media skirmish over H-1Bs. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=
=80=99s ridiculous, because I=E2=80=99m a Trump loyalist and now I=E2=80=99=
m being punished. I am the most loyal Trump supporter out there,=E2=80=9D L=
oomer told me.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;">Musk=E2=80=99s wealth and staggering influence has i=
nsulated him from a reckoning with the broader MAGA faithful, at least
for now. He=E2=80=99s still at the epicenter of power, but there=E2=80=99s =
a strain of suspicion toward him among Trump=E2=80=99s original disciples=
=E2=80=94specifically, the white working-class coalition that Bannon helped=
 amass, in 2016, and that are a different breed from the Musk-led legion of=
 tech megadonors, crypto bros, and Gen Z fanboys who converted for Trump in=
 2024. The Bannon and Musk camps together helped send Trump back to the Whi=
te House. But with their shared Democratic enemy vanquished, they=E2=80=99v=
e turned their
guns on each other.</p></div>
